channel.title: [Release] Project Corrupted [Release]
channel.description:
[NEWS] Pictures weren't working, so I put direct links instead. If none of them work, please report it to me via private messaging. [NEWS]
Well, this [b]IS[/b] a DeltaScape base, so please don't flame for that, but I've been working on it for a while, and I've just gotten tired of coding, so with this release, I'll be leaving the coding system. I'll hang around the forums and talk though.
Server Credits: Delta_, Myself, Rog3r (For some help on different parts even though he didn't know it), Goth Wolf (Thanks for the Godsword Hilts/Blade coding bro!)
Client Credits: Delta_, Myself, SilentCJ (Models, love 'em bro!) and some of the other people around MoparScape for models (If you notice a model in here that was yours and you have proof it was your model, post and I'll add your name), Goth Wolf (Hilts/Blade Models & Ints, Thanks bro!)
Well, this server is NOT for the non-realistic fans, so if you like everything super easy and non-realistic, please LEAVE THIS TOPIC NOW!
This server is based Realistic, with working Slayer Caves, Slayer Towers, Brimhaven Dragon Dungeon (Almost 100%) and Taverly Dungeon, with Hill Giant caves underneath of Edgeville/Varrock and a working Crystal Key chest with Tooth/Loop Half Keys.
There are also some Guilds which require Premium and 99 in a skill to enter + Some items that are only for people with 99 in a skill and have Premium. You can remove Premium if you want or just make it so you need like 2-4 99's to get premium, it's up to you.
Keep in mind, this server has all of the normal stuff DeltaScape had; Pest Control, Full Wilderness, Quests, etc. I take NO CREDITS for ANY of that. Just for the stuff I did even though it was extremely easy to do.

~~~ Quick TuT on changing the hidden IP in the client ~~~
In the client, open up the client class (client.java) and then search for: [code]setserver[/code]
You should see this: [code] setserver("project-corrupted.no-ip.org", "43594");[/code]
And if you search it again, you should see the exact same thing later down the line:
[code] setserver("project-corrupted.no-ip.org", "43594");[/code]
Change the project-corrupted.no-ip.org in BOTH of them to whatever you want. Leave it blank for no IP to be set, or set your own IP, it's up to you.
Was hoping common sense would kick in from here, but all right.. [b]After[/b] changing the IP, make sure to SAVE the client.java, then hit "Compile". If it comes back with something like:
[code]The system cannot find the path specified. Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
Then you need to edit the JDK that the compiler uses.
Right click the compile.bat and hit "Edit", then you'll see this:
[code]@echo off Title RedrumScape Compiler "C:Program FilesJavajdk1.6.0_10injavac.exe" *.java pause [/code]
Change the 10 there to whatever update of JDK your using (6, 7, 8, whatever). Save, and then try running it. If you did it right, it'll say:
[code]Note: EconomyBoost.java uses or overrides a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
Congratulations, fixed.. [center][img]http://www.moparisthebest.org/smf/Themes/default/images/warnwarn.gif[/img] Saying stuff like 'post or ill remove' is against the rules. I have removed it from the topic and given you a warning.[/center]

item.dc:creator: @King_Redrum King Redrum
item.description:
@King_Redrum wrote:

Wearing.java controls the levels required to wear certain items. Here’s an example:

Search;

GetCLAttack

Anything under this results in an Attack level to wear that item, example;

} else if (ItemName.startsWith("Saradomin godsword")) { return 75;

What that means is;

} else if (ItemName.startsWith("Saradomin godsword")) {

If the item name is/starts with Saradomin godsword,

return 75;

Tells the person that they need 75 Attack to wear that item, and does NOT allow them to equip it if they are 74 or lower attack, while if they are 75+ attack, they can wear it.
